## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="716d9-140">在以下示例中，方法返回包含已识别的短语的语义的 SML 的字符串。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-140">In the following example, a method returns a string that contains the SML for the semantics of a recognized phrase.</span></span>  
  
```  
private string GetSemanticsSML(RecognizedPhrase result)  
{  
  if (result.Semantics.Count > 0)  
  {  
    return result.ConstructSmlFromSemantics().CreateNavigator().OuterXml;  
  }  
  else  
  {  
    return null;  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="716d9-161">语音识别语法可以包含语义信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-161">A speech recognition grammar can include semantic information.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="716d9-162">当语音识别器生成此类语法的识别结果时，可能会根据所语法和到识别器输入的规则在识别结果中，包含的语义信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-162">When a speech recognizer generates a recognition result for such a grammar, the semantic information might be included in the recognition result, according to the rules of the grammar and the input to the recognizer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="716d9-163">有关语义信息的详细信息，请参阅[了解语义结果](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2a9dbd8b-cf6d-42cd-bbb9-ca0b3e534005)并<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey>和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue>类。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-163">For more information about semantic information, see [Understanding Semantic Results](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/2a9dbd8b-cf6d-42cd-bbb9-ca0b3e534005) and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> classes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="716d9-164">下面的示例定义一个方法，可获取特定的语义信息中已识别的短语。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-164">The following example defines a method that gets specific semantic information from a recognized phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="716d9-165">此方法返回时，它包含的语义键或为 null 的值，如果不检索的值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-165">When this method returns, it contains the value for the semantic key, or null if the value was not retrieved.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="716d9-166">此方法只检查顶级项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-166">This method checks only for top-level keys.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="716d9-167">由于语义信息包含在值的树中，必须通过返回的语义值访问较低级别的项。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="716d9-167">Since the semantic information is contained in a tree of values, lower-level keys must be accessed through the returned semantic value.</span></span>  
  
```  
static bool TryGetSemanticValue(  
      RecognizedPhrase phrase, string key, out SemanticValue value)  
{  
  value = null;  
  bool found = phrase.Semantics.ContainsKey(key);  
  if (found)  
  {  
    value = phrase.Semantics[key];  
  }  
  
  return found;  
}  
```
